This paper deals with the problem of computing a subnetwork in a communication network that allows messages to be transmitted with minimum energy. This problem is closely related to the field of network optimization, which falls under the category of computer networks and communications (cs.NI). The paper also proposes a protocol for computing the subnetwork, which involves algorithms and data structures, falling under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the use of information theory in the context of energy-efficient communication, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT). The paper also proposes a protocol for computing the subnetwork, which involves control and optimization, falling under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the performance improvements obtained through simulation, which falls under the category of game theory and economics (cs.GT).
